They've been enjoying life together after being forced to keep their relationship secret for months.

But despite finally stepping out into the public eye, Matty 'J' Johnson and Laura Byrne appear unwilling to send each other a Facebook friend request.

A search of Matty's near-five thousand friends on the social network doesn't return a result for his new accessories designer girlfriend.

Scroll down for videos

Matty 'J' Johnson and Laura Byrne appear unwilling to send each other a Facebook friend request, as the pair appear to be unconnected on the social network

A search of Matty's near-five thousand friends on the social network doesn't return a result for his new accessories designer girlfriend

It remains unclear whether her no-show is related to strict privacy settings, or if the pair are bizarrely not 'Facebook official' - or even connected at all.

It's doubly strange as on Friday, Laura Byrne made their relationship official on her Instagram account to her 98,000 followers.

The 30-year-old uploaded two snaps, one of them smiling at the camera, and in the next photo the hunky marketing director, who was sporting a rugged look, kisses his lady on the cheek.

Matty professed his love for Bachelor winner Laura during the show's dramatic finale on Thursday, after seven weeks together on the matchmaking series.

The Sydney-based hunk confirmed on Friday he previously crossed paths with the accessories designer before her limousine arrived in the premiere.

Insta-love: It's doubly strange as on Friday, Laura Byrne made their relationship official on her Instagram account to her 98,000 followers

Close: The 30-year-old uploaded two snaps, one of them smiling at the camera, and in the next photo the hunky marketing director, who was sporting a rugged look, kisses his lady on the cheek

Speaking on The Project on Friday night, Matty said: 'We bumped into each other at a sauna.'

Breaking hearts with every rose ceremony elimination, Matty J previously admitted that he wish he could have sent the other 20 girls home in favour of Laura on the first night.

'On our first date we started to talk and we realised we had a few friends in common and we realised that we bumped into each other at a sauna,' the marketing manager confessed to The Project panel.

'We had some sliding door moments': Matty J and Laura reveaed they crossed paths in Bondi before the show but were too nervous to speak to each other

'It's kind of ironic that it took a TV show to bring us together': Matty claimed the pair have friends in common and would frequent the same areas and venues before the show

He continued: 'We were at a sauna at Icebergs and we clocked each other, but we never said a word and it's kind of ironic that it took a TV show to bring us together.'

'I recognised him because he had his shirt off,' Laura joked, holding Matty's hand during the interview.

The brunette beauty described the chance meeting: 'I was there with a friend and I was like, "I think that's the guy from The Bachelorette" and that was all, there was no conversation.'

'I recognised him because he had his shirt off': Laura joked that she knew she had bumped into Matty J because he was showing off his abs in the sauna
